org.team5940.robot_core.modules.logging

Interface LoggerModule

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Module
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractLoggerModule, AggregateLoggerModule, FileLoggerModule, MultipleLoggerModule, SelectableLoggerModule, SystemLoggerModule

    public interface LoggerModule
extends Module
    This interface is for a Module that logs.

      static LoggerModule INERT_LOGGER

    • Field Detail

      • INERT_LOGGER

        static final LoggerModule INERT_LOGGER
        This logger, named "inert_logger", should be used whenever you want a logger that doesn't do anything. It also serves as the basis of the logging framework, otherwise you wouldn't be able to initialize loggers that log internally.

        void setEnabled(boolean enabled)

        Parameters:
        enabled - True if this should output logs, false otherwise.

      • checkInitializationArg

        default void checkInitializationArg(Module module,
                                    java.lang.Class<? extends Module> constructorClass,
                                    java.lang.Object arg)
                             throws java.lang.IllegalArgumentException
        Used to check whether an implementation of Module is being initialized with a null argument. If so, logs an error and throws an exception for you. Should be placed at the beginning of the constructor (but after super constructor calls if applicable).
        Parameters:
        module - The module that is initializing.
        constructorClass - The class of the module that is initializing.
        arg - The argument that the module is initializing with.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - Thrown if arg is null.
        See Also:
        checkInitializationArgs(Module, Class, Object[])

      • checkInitializationArgs

        default void checkInitializationArgs(Module module,
                                     java.lang.Class<? extends Module> constructorClass,
                                     java.lang.Object[] args)
                              throws java.lang.IllegalArgumentException
        Used to check whether an implementation of Module is being initialized with null arguments. If so, logs an error with them and throws an exception for you. Should be placed at the beginning of the constructor (but after super constructor calls if applicable).
        Parameters:
        module - The module that is initializing.
        constructorClass - The class of the module that is initializing.
        args - The arguments that the module is initializing with.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - Thrown if any object in args is null.
        See Also:
        checkInitializationArg(Module, Class, Object)
